  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      It is believed that children with a prior history of significant burn injury continue to
      manifest low levels of antioxidants well into their convalescence.The purpose of this study
      is to examine malondialdehyde (an oxidative lipid marker) and vitamins E, C and beta carotene
      status in reconstructive burn patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
